There are ⌈a ÷ b⌉ − 1 positive multiples of b below a.
So, the sum of the multiples of 3 and 5 below 100 is:

3T_(⌈1000÷3⌉ − 1) + 5T_(⌈1000÷5⌉ − 1) − 15T_(⌈1000÷15⌉ − 1)
Multiples of 3     Multiples of 5     Where they overlap

3T_333 + 5T_199 − 15T_66

3/2 (333² + 333) + 5/2 (199² + 199) − 15/2 (66² + 66)

(3 × 111222 + 5 × 39800 − 15 × 4422) ÷ 2

3 × 55611 + 5 × 19900 − 15 × 2211

